The paper discusses the concept of intrinsic dimension of a dataset, which is a fundamental concept in machine learning and data analysis. The paper proposes an axiomatic approach to this concept, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field of machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
